com.nitin.json.pointer

Class JsonPointer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nitin.json.pointer.JsonPointer

  • public class JsonPointer
extends Object
    Author:
    Nitin Patel This class is an implementation of "JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Pointer" RFC 6901: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6901 The implementation is based on jackson library, and takes jackson's org.codehaus.jackson.JsonNode as input and output.

      • getValue

        public org.codehaus.jackson.JsonNode getValue(org.codehaus.jackson.JsonNode node)
                                       throws JsonPointerException
        Evaluates the current jsonPointer against the Json document which is provided as an input, and returns the Json which refers to the current pointer. Usage: JsonPointer jsonPointer = new JsonPointer("/foo/0"); JsonNode node = jsonPointer.getValue(inputJson));//say inputJson represents {"foo": ["bar", "baz"]} Note: With {"foo": ["bar", "baz"]} as input Json document, and "/foo/0" as json pointer, this method would return "bar" as the output.
        Parameters:
        node - - Represents the Json document against which the json pointer needs to be evaluated.
        Returns:
        Json which refers to the current json pointer.
        Throws:
        JsonPointerException - - If the json pointer is invalid or if the evaluation fails on the json document provided as input.
